bio:
I'm a **Pre-Doctoral Researcher** at **Inria Paris** in the **ALMAnaCH** team, working under the supervision of [Djam√© Seddah](https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=P7EtARsAAAAJ&hl=fr) on **Mechanistic Interpretability** and **LLM safety**. My research focuses on understanding the internal mechanisms of LLMs, how they represent and process language, and how we can use that understanding to improve them.

I worked with [Armel Randy Zebaze](https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=mhVpw1UAAAAJ&hl=fr), whose PhD focuses on low-resource machine translation, on **disentangling sentence equivalence from target language** in LLM-based translation. I also worked with [Wissam Antoun](https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=fEgsyU4AAAAJ&hl=en), who worked on the training of the Gaperon French LLM suite, on studying **how triggers hijack model representations** to induce backdoor behaviors.

As part of my work at Inria, I also ran **continuous pre-training** of the **Gaperon** models across multiple nodes, and built an end-to-end evaluation library that automates **LLM benchmarking** on **HPC**, making it easier to run evaluations at scale with Slurm.

On the side, I'm building **Straufi**, a no-code platform for **designing and backtesting automated trading strategies**, which placed 3rd at the EFREI Innovation Project (awarded by Microsoft, Thales, and Capgemini officials). I hold an **M.S. in Computer Science** from **EFREI Paris** with a major in **Data & AI**, and spent a semester at **UC Irvine**.

When not doing research, I train and compete in kickboxing ü•ä
